You are also putting a bigger load on the engine, thus creating more heat.  

You know all this VW overheating talk has always had me wondering, why does
a Porsche 356 engine run so cool? They have the same style oil cooler as a
VW, in the shroud, 36 HP style shroud, they do have bigger heads and an oil
filter, duel carbs etc. When I use to drive my 356 (1960) to Havasu from
Cali, I would cruise at 80-90 mph in 100 degree plus heat and my oil temp
never would go above 210. The 356 has a smaller crank pully then a VW and
the cooling fan is the same as a 36 hp engine, kust makes me wonder. I think
I'll see if I can fit some 356 heads to a VW case. 

ronnie

ps. The pre A Porsches  engine case was the same as a 36 hp VW

